import re import sys
arg_url = " ".join(sys.argv[1:])
def extract_url(markdown_link): url = re.search('\((.*?)\)', markdown_link) return url.group(1) if url else None
sys.stdout.write(extract_url(arg_url)) # Outputs: www.google.com

Various hotkeys to capture ideas and urls directly to your obsidian daily note.
## Setup Install and setup the Shimmering Obsidian workflow.
Define dailynote format in configure workflow section. `dailynote_%Y-%m-%d` for `dailynote_YYYY-MM-DD`. Uses python's datetime strftime formatting rules.
## Cheatsheet - Shift-Command-C - Copy current browser tabs URL+Title as a markdown link - Shift-Command-A - Copy current browser tab as markdown link but have option to append - Enter - #Journal - Control - #Ideas - Shift - #Todos - Shift-Command-F - Search for current browers's tab in notes - jt <text> - Appends text under "Todo" header in daily note - jj <text> - Appends text under "Journal" - ji <text> - Appends text under "Ideas" - `f <text>` searches for str in notes, script filter of matches will pop up to goto note. - # TODO - connect to add to daily note workflow
